00:00:29.280 --> 00:00:34.219
Metaskin can make things invisible to radar.

00:00:34.219 --> 00:00:39.249
The stretchable material, developed at Iowa
State University, manipulates electromagnetic

00:00:39.249 --> 00:00:42.679
waves using electric rings filled with liquid
metal.

00:00:42.679 --> 00:00:48.219
The rings absorb radar frequency waves, so
an object covered in this material would essentially

00:00:48.219 --> 00:00:51.570
be impossible to detect using radar.

00:00:51.570 --> 00:00:56.979
In the 70 years since PET plastics have been
in existence, a bacterium has already evolved

00:00:56.979 --> 00:00:58.339
to eat it.

00:00:58.339 --> 00:01:02.889
Researchers in Japan discovered the species
attaching to PET with tendril-like threads

00:01:02.889 --> 00:01:08.729
and using two enzymes to break it down into
its original substances which aren’t environmentally

00:01:08.729 --> 00:01:09.729
harmful.

00:01:09.729 --> 00:01:14.810
The goal now is to speed up the process which
currently takes about six weeks to eat a thumbnail-sized

00:01:14.810 --> 00:01:16.140
piece.

00:01:16.140 --> 00:01:20.229
Computer vision is being used to find the
exact image you’re looking for.

00:01:20.229 --> 00:01:25.140
Taking a huge leap forward in 2012, computer
vision is now used in Facebook’s facial

00:01:25.140 --> 00:01:30.329
recognition, which was featured in Mind Blow
#80, as well as Google’s image CAPTCHA.

00:01:30.329 --> 00:01:35.369
Image searches are typically hampered by keywords,
which works okay if you want to find any old

00:01:35.369 --> 00:01:39.680
picture of a blue bike but not great if you
need a very specific blue bike.

00:01:39.680 --> 00:01:44.760
Shutterstock’s new computer vision model
uses an image's raw pixel data to understand

00:01:44.760 --> 00:01:49.460
what is contained within the image, enabling
it to break the image down into its dominant

00:01:49.460 --> 00:01:54.259
features that can be used to find visually
similar images, as well as perform a reverse

00:01:54.259 --> 00:01:57.079
image search of 70 million images.

00:01:57.079 --> 00:02:00.360
All of this occurring in double-digit milliseconds.

00:02:00.360 --> 00:02:05.189
Advances in computer vision will aid automated
vehicles and robot sight.

00:02:05.189 --> 00:02:09.119
Researchers have proven a technique that allows
kidneys to be donated to anyone.

00:02:09.119 --> 00:02:13.519
Traditionally, a compatible donor would not
only need the right blood type, but also the

00:02:13.519 --> 00:02:16.340
correct combination of 6 antigens.

00:02:16.340 --> 00:02:18.590
The chances of which are 1 in 100,000.

00:02:18.590 --> 00:02:24.670
Sadly, around 4,500 people in the U.S. alone,
die annually waiting for that match.

00:02:24.670 --> 00:02:29.489
But with their Desensitization technique,
new antigens are regenerated that are less

00:02:29.489 --> 00:02:35.340
likely to attack a newly transplanted organ,
lessening the chance for rejection and increasing

00:02:35.340 --> 00:02:36.510
the chance of survival.

00:02:36.510 --> 00:02:40.650
A potential game changer for kidney transplants.

00:02:40.650 --> 00:02:43.489
Nima is a portable gluten sensor.

00:02:43.489 --> 00:02:48.209
By putting a sample of the food in a disposable
capsule, the sensors in the device tell you

00:02:48.209 --> 00:02:52.900
if there’s 20 parts per million or more
of gluten and then display the results on

00:02:52.900 --> 00:02:55.459
the front - with an accuracy of 99.5%.

00:02:55.459 --> 00:03:01.970
And they’re currently developing tests to
launch a similar device for peanuts and dairy.

